==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cocker spaniel
<hw>Cock"er span"iel</hw>. <def>One of a breed of small or medium-sized
spaniels kept for hunting or retrieving game or for household pets. They
usually weigh from eighteen to twenty-eight pounds. They have the head
of fair length, with square muzzle, the ears long and set low, the legs
short or of medium length, and the coat fine and silky, wavy but not
curly. Various colors are bred, as black, liver, red, black and white,
black and tan, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

